<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-29T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Mexico/411: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-29T12:00:00-06:00">February 29, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:30
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>40. Referring to the Embassy’s despatch No. 3238, President today
                                signed decree designed to prevent alcohol smuggling which will
                                appear in <hi rend="italic">Diario Oficial</hi> on Monday.<note n="49" xml:id="d350fn49">The Mexican decree was promulgated on
                                    March 9 and published in the <hi rend="italic">Diario
                                        Oficial</hi> of March 12, entering into effect on March
                                    22.</note> Please notify the Treasury Department.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>